        massive brown dwarf (BD) or even a low-mass M-dwarf seen nearly
        face-on. To our knowledge, the nature of HD 114762 b is still
        undetermined. The astrometric noise measured for this system in
        the first data release, DR1, of the Gaia mission allows us to
        derive new constraints on the astrometric motion of HD 114762
        and on the mass of its companion. We use the method GASTON,
        introduced in a preceding paper, which can simulate Gaia data
        and determine the distribution of inclinations that are
